src/ittf/examples/jswizzi/quick.js.ittf



   1 module
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var JsWizziContext = require('../../lib/jswizzi/jsWizziContext')
   4     var jsWizziRunner = require('../../lib/jswizzi/jsWizziRunner')
   5     var result
   6         _ runExpression
   7             @ 'var x = typeof(nemo); return x;'
   8     log 'result', result
   9     function runExpression
  10         param code
  11         # without ctor arguments means: isForInterpolation
  12         var jsWizziContext
  13             new JsWizziContext()
  14         # run the expression embedded in a var declaration 'result'
  15         var hr
  16             _ jsWizziRunner.run
  17                 iif code.indexOf('return ') > -1
  18                     then 'var result = function dummy() { ' + code + ' }();'
  19                     else 'var result = ' + code + ';'
  20                 @ jsWizziContext
  21                 {
  22                     @ verbose false
  23         if hr && hr.__is_error
  24             throw new Error(hr)
  25         # return the 'result' var from the context
  26         return jsWizziContext.getValue('result')

src/ittf/examples/loader/step_2__copy/t/repeater.sample.ittf



   1 $group
   2     $params name, items, from|0
   3     var len_${name} = ${items}.length
   4     function repeater_${name}
   5         param index_${name}
   6         if index_${name} === len_${name}
   7             return
   8                 _ next_${name}
   9         var item_${name} = ${items}[index_${name}]
  10         $hook
  11     _ repeater_${name}(${from})
  12     function next_${name}
  13         $hook next

src/ittf/examples/loader/step_2__copy/appender_1.sample.ittf



   1 append 1
   2     $
   3         var do = 1;
   4     $if do = 0
   5         repeater( 1,  items)
   6             log 1
   7             if a
   8                 log 2
   9                 if b
  10                     log 3
  11                     repeater( 2,  items,  index_1 + 1)
  12                         log 4
  13                         if c
  14                             log 5
  15                             repeater_increment( 2)
  16                         $append next
  17                             log 6
  18             log 7
  19             if d
  20                 repeater_increment( 1)
  21             $append next
  22                 log 8
  23     $if do = 1
  24         repeater( 1,  model.statements)
  25             log '607 jsArray'
  26             if u.isMemberAccessOrCall(item_1)
  27                 _ ctx.w('')
  28                 _ ctx.deindent()
  29                 _ ctx.write(']')
  30                 log '605 jsArray'
  31                 return
  32                     _ cnt.genItem
  33                         @ item_1
  34                         @ ctx
  35                         f_cb()
  36                             log '603 jsArray'
  37                             repeater( 2,  model.statements,  index_1 + 1)
  38                                 if u.isCallArgument(item_2)
  39                                     _ ctx.write('.')
  40                                 _ cnt.genItem
  41                                     @ item_2
  42                                     @ ctx
  43                                     f_cb()
  44                                         repeater_increment( 2)
  45                                 $append next
  46                                     r_cb()
  47             log '606 jsArray'
  48             if !first
  49                 _ ctx.w(', ')
  50             set first = false
  51             _ cnt.genItem
  52                 @ item_1
  53                 @ ctx
  54                 f_cb()
  55                     log '604 jsArray'
  56                     repeater_increment( 1)
  57             $append next
  58                 + ;
  59                 _ ctx.w('')
  60                 _ ctx.deindent()
  61                 _ ctx.write(']')
  62                 r_cb()

src/ittf/examples/t/example_prints.js.ittf



   1 $group
   2     $params name, level|0, step|1
   3     function heading1
   4         param text
   5         log ''
   6         log '*'.repeat(120)
   7         log '** level ${level} - step ${step} - ${name} - ' + text
   8         log '*'.repeat(120)
   9         log ''
  10     function heading2
  11         param text
  12         log ''
  13         log '   ', '-'.repeat(100)
  14         log '   ','-- ${name} - ' + text
  15         log '   ', '-'.repeat(100)
  16         log ''
  17     function printArray
  18         param name
  19         param arr
  20         param fields
  21         param format
  22         if format === 'dashes'
  23             log '   ', '-'.repeat(100)
  24         log '   ', '* array ' + name + ' : '
  25         foreach item in arr
  26             log '    {', i
  27             var keys = fields || Object.keys(item)
  28             foreach k in keys
  29                 _ printValue
  30                     @ k
  31                     @ item[k]
  32     function printValue
  33         param k
  34         param v
  35         param format
  36         param p1
  37         if format === 'dashes' || format === 'meter'
  38             log '   ', '-'.repeat(100)
  39         if format === 'json'
  40             set v
  41                 _ stringify
  42                     @ v
  43                     @ null
  44                     @ 4
  45         if verify.isNotEmpty(v)
  46             var lines
  47                 _ verify.splitLines
  48                     @ v
  49                     {
  50                         @ numbered true
  51             if lines.length === 1
  52                 log '   ', k, ':', lines[0].text
  53             else
  54                 for var i=0; i<lines.length; i++
  55                     if i === 0
  56                         log '   ', k, ':', lines[0].numFmt, lines[0].text
  57                     else
  58                         log '   ', spaces(k.length+1), ' ', lines[i].numFmt, lines[i].text
  59         elif verify.isObject(v)
  60             log '   ', k, ':', inspect(v)
  61         else
  62             log '   ', k, ':', v
  63         if format === 'meter'
  64             _ meterLine(p1, '     ' + new Array(1 + k.length).join(' '))
  65     function printObject
  66         param k
  67         param v
  68         param format
  69         param p1
  70         if format === 'dashes' || format === 'meter'
  71             log '   ', '-'.repeat(100)
  72         log '   ', k, '{'
  73         _ __printObject(v, 2, 6)
  74         if format === 'meter'
  75             _ meterLine(p1, '     ' + new Array(1 + k.length).join(' '))
  76     function __printObject
  77         param v
  78         param level
  79         param limit
  80         if level < limit
  81             var indent = new Array(1 + level * 4).join(' ')
  82             var prop
  83             for var k in v
  84                 set prop = v[k]
  85                 if verify.isObject(prop)
  86                     log indent, k, '{'
  87                     _ __printObject(prop, level+1, limit)
  88                 elif verify.isFunction(prop)
  89                     log indent, k, 'function'
  90                 elif verify.isArray(prop)
  91                     log indent, k, '['
  92                     var indent2 = new Array(1 + (level+1) * 4).join(' ')
  93                     foreach item in prop
  94                         if verify.isObject(item)
  95                             _ __printObject(item, level+1, limit)
  96                         elif verify.isFunction(item)
  97                             log indent2, 'function'
  98                         else
  99                             log indent2, item
 100                 else
 101                     log indent, k, prop
 102     function spaces
 103         param len
 104         return new Array(len).join(' ')
 105     function meterLine
 106         param len
 107         param indent
 108         var sb = []
 109         var numW = len < 10 ? 1 : ( len < 100 ? 2 : 3 )
 110         var x
 111         for var i=0; i<numW; i++
 112             for var j=0; j<len; j++
 113                 set x = formatNum(j, numW)
 114                 _ sb.push(x.substr(i,1))
 115             log indent, sb.join('')
 116             set sb = []
 117     function formatNum
 118         param num
 119         param len
 120         var x = num.toString()
 121         return new Array(1 + len-x.length).join(' ') + x

src/ittf/examples/t/oldexample.js.ittf



   1 module
   2     $params name
   3     kind jsfile
   4     +
   5     import path

   9     var mocks = require('../../tests/loader/mocks/misc')
  10     var mTreeLoader = require('../../tests/loader/mocks/mTreeLoader')
  11     set module.exports
  12         function
  13             var
  14                 decl store
  15                 decl evaluatedModel
  16             log 1
  17             set store = new mocks.IttfDocumentStore()
  18             log 2
  19             _ store.init

src/ittf/lib/basicloader/liner.js.ittf



   1 module
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var util = require('util')
   4     #
   5         # Reads an IttfDocument and extract an array of line descriptions
   6     #
   7         # params
   8         # string textContent
   9         # #  The text content of the IttfDocument
  10         # { ittfDocumentData
  11         # string sourceKey
  12         # # The IttfDocument key generated by the loadHistory
  13     #
  14         # Output
  15         # lines:Array of
  16         # line : {
  17         # indent: Number,
  18         # name: String,
  19         # value: String, // always trimmed
  20         # row: Number,
  21         # col: Number,
  22         # sourceKey: String,
  23         # tagSuffix: undefined || '(',
  24         # hasMacro: Boolean
  25         # }
  26     #
  27         # Ittf commands for comments
  28         # $ and $ ... singleline comment
  29         # $ and * ... * and $ multiline comment
  30         # Comment states
  31         # 0 = no comment seen
  32         # 1 = seen char $ could be first char of comment
  33         # 2 = seen chars $ and * we are inside multiline comments
  34         # 3 = seen chars $ and * ... and *  could be first char of end of multiline comments
  35         # 21 = seen chars $ and $ we are inside singleline comment
  36         # Es6 macro states
  37         # 0 = no macro seen
  38         # 1 = seen char ` we are inside macro
  39         # 2 = seen escape char inside a macro, the next ` char does not close the macro string
  40     set module.exports
  41         function
  42             param textContent
  43             param ittfDocumentData
  44             var
  45                 decl sourceKey = ittfDocumentData.sourceKey
  46                 decl lines
  47                     [
  48                 decl leadingWhiteSpaces = 0
  49                 decl line = null
  50                 decl linepos = 1
  51                 decl lineHasMacro = false
  52                 decl colpos = 0
  53                 decl commentState = 0
  54                 decl macroState = 0
  55                 decl quote = null
  56                 # TODO ensure textContent is red as utf-8 and avoid this
  57                 decl chunk = textContent.toString('utf-8')
  58                 decl ch
  59                 decl chUni
  60                 decl i
  61                 decl l = chunk.length
  62             # TODO replace ch with chUni
  63             for i = 0; i < l; i++
  64                 set ch = chunk[i]
  65                 set chUni = chunk.charCodeAt(i)
  66                 set colpos++
  67                 if quote != null
  68                     if quote == ch
  69                         set quote = null
  70                     _ processMacro(ch)
  71                 else
  72                     if commentState == 2
  73                         if ch == '*'
  74                             # could be start of end of comment
  75                             set commentState = 3
  76                         else
  77                             # skip comment char
  78                             if ch == '\n'
  79                                 set linepos++
  80                                 set colpos = 0
  81                     elif commentState == 21
  82                         if ch == '\n'
  83                             # end of line comment
  84                             # delegate end of comment to processMacro
  85                             _ processMacro(ch)
  86                     elif commentState == 3
  87                         if ch == '$'
  88                             # ok, really is end of comment
  89                             set commentState = 0
  90                         else
  91                             # no, comments continue
  92                             set commentState = 2
  93                             # check if it is eol
  94                             if ch == '\n'
  95                                 set linepos++
  96                                 set colpos = 0
  97                     elif commentState == 1 && ch == '*'
  98                         # ok, really is start of comment
  99                         set commentState = 2
 100                     elif commentState == 1 && ch == '$'
 101                         # ok, is a line comment
 102                         set commentState = 21
 103                     elif commentState == 1 && ch != '*'
 104                         # no, it was not a comment, reset
 105                         set commentState = 0
 106                         _ processMacro('$')
 107                         _ processMacro(ch)
 108                     elif commentState == 0 && ch == '"'
 109                         # start of literal
 110                         set quote = ch
 111                         _ processMacro(ch)
 112                     elif commentState == 0 && ch == "'"
 113                         # start of literal
 114                         set quote = ch
 115                         _ processMacro(ch)
 116                     elif commentState == 0 && ch == '$'
 117                         # could be start of comment
 118                         set commentState = 1
 119                     else
 120                         _ processMacro(ch)
 121             if line
 122                 if typeof (line.value) !== 'undefined'
 123                     set line.value = line.value.trim()
 124                 set line.hasMacro = lineHasMacro
 125                 _ lines.push(line)
 126                 set lineHasMacro = false
 127             return lines
 128             function processMacro
 129                 param ch
 130                 if macroState == 2
 131                     # remove escape state
 132                     set macroState = 1
 133                     # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 134                 else
 135                     if chUni == 96
 136                         if macroState > 0
 137                             set macroState = 0
 138                             # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 139                         else
 140                             set macroState = 1
 141                             # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 142                     else
 143                         if macroState == 1
 144                             if ch == '$'
 145                                 set ch = '#'
 146                                 set lineHasMacro = true
 147                                 # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 148                             elif ch == '\\'
 149                                 # could be an escape of a macro inside a macro
 150                                 set macroState = 2
 151                                 # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 152                 _ processChar(ch)
 153             function processChar
 154                 param ch
 155                 if ch == '\n'
 156                     if line
 157                         if typeof (line.value) !== 'undefined'
 158                             set line.value = line.value.trim()
 159                         set line.hasMacro = lineHasMacro
 160                         _ lines.push(line)
 161                         set line = null
 162                         set lineHasMacro = false
 163                     else
 164                         # Allow blank line. Do nothing
 165                     set leadingWhiteSpaces = 0
 166                     set colpos = 0
 167                     set linepos++
 168                     if commentState != 2
 169                         set commentState = 0
 170                 elif ch == '\r'
 171                 elif [' ', '\t'].indexOf(ch) !== -1
 172                     if ch == '\t'
 173                         set colpos += 3
 174                     if line
 175                         if typeof (line.value) == 'undefined'
 176                             set line.value = ''
 177                         else
 178                             set line.value += ch
 179                     else
 180                         set leadingWhiteSpaces += ch == ' ' ? 1 : 4
 181                 elif ['('].indexOf(ch) !== -1
 182                     if line
 183                         if typeof (line.value) == 'undefined'
 184                             set line.tagSuffix = ch
 185                             set line.value = ''
 186                         else
 187                             set line.value += ch
 188                     else
 189                         set line =
 190                             {
 191                                 @ indent leadingWhiteSpaces / 4
 192                                 @ name ch
 193                                 @ row linepos
 194                                 @ col colpos
 195                                 @ sourceKey sourceKey
 196                 else
 197                     if line
 198                         if typeof(line.value) == 'undefined'
 199                             set line.name += ch
 200                         else
 201                             set line.value += ch
 202                     else
 203                         set line =
 204                             {
 205                                 @ indent leadingWhiteSpaces / 4
 206                                 @ name ch
 207                                 @ row linepos
 208                                 @ col colpos
 209                                 @ sourceKey sourceKey

src/ittf/lib/basicloader/mTree.js.ittf

src/ittf/lib/basicloader/nodifier.js.ittf



   1 module
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var util = require('util')
   4     #
   5         # Nodify the lines of an IttfDocument and creates a
   6         # tree structure object based on line indentation.
   7         # . detects the $params command
   8         # . implements line continuation
   9         # . assigns an id to each node
  10         # !!! A line object is transformed in place into a node object
  11         # without recreation (no cloning) !!!
  12         #
  13         # Inputs
  14         # - the lines produced by the liner
  15         # Outputs
  16         # nodes: Array of [
  17         # line -> mTreeNode : {
  18         # + parent: Object, // parent mTreeNode
  19         # + model: Object, // the MTreeBrick to which the line belongs
  20         # + children: Array, // the children mTreeNodes
  21         # id: Number,
  22         # indent: Number,
  23         # name: String,
  24         # value: String,
  25         # row: Number,
  26         # col: Number,
  27         # sourceKey: String,
  28         # tagSuffix: undefined || '('
  29         # hasMacro: Boolean
  30         # }
  31         # ]
  32         #
  33         # Ittf commands:
  34         # $params  // the param values are stored in the MTreeBrick
  35         # \        // implements line continuation
  36         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  37         # //   without separators
  38         # \b       // implements line continuation
  39         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  40         # //   with a space separator:  prevLine,value += ' ' + currentLine.value
  41         # \n       // implements line continuation
  42         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  43         # //   with a line break separator:  prevLine,value += '\n' + currentLine.value
  44         #
  45     set module.exports
  46         function
  47             param lines
  48             param mTree
  49             var
  50                 decl nodes
  51                     [
  52                 decl root = null
  53                 decl current = null
  54                 decl nameFirstChar = null
  55                 decl nameLength = 0
  56                 decl line
  57                 decl i
  58                 decl l = lines.length
  59             for var i = 0; i < l; i++
  60                 set line = lines[i]
  61                 set nameFirstChar = line.name[0]
  62                 set nameLength = line.name.length
  63                 set line.id = mTree.getNewNodeId()
  64                 set line.model = mTree
  65                 if line.indent == 0 && current == null
  66                     set line.parent = null
  67                     _ nodes.push(line)
  68                 elif current == null
  69                     return
  70                         _ error
  71                             @ 'Malformed tree, root node cannot have an indent.'
  72                             @ line
  73                             @ mTree
  74                 elif line.indent == current.indent
  75                     if typeof(current.parent) === 'undefined' || current.parent === null
  76                         return
  77                             _ error
  78                                 @ 'Malformed tree, only one root note allowed.'
  79                                 @ line
  80                                 @ mTree
  81                     set line.parent = current.parent
  82                     _ current.parent.children.push(line)
  83                 elif line.indent > current.indent
  84                     if nameFirstChar == '$' && line.name === '$params'
  85                         if current.indent > 0
  86                             return
  87                                 _ error
  88                                     @ 'The $params node must be a child of the root node.'
  89                                     @ line
  90                                     @ mTree
  91                         set current.model.$params = line.value
  92                         continue
  93                     elif nameFirstChar == '\\' && nameLength == 1
  94                         # value continuation on new line
  95                         set current.value += line.value
  96                         continue
  97                     elif nameFirstChar == '\\' && line.name === '\\b'
  98                         # value continuation on new line with space
  99                         set current.value += (' ' + line.value)
 100                         continue
 101                     elif nameFirstChar == '\\' && line.name === '\\n'
 102                         # value continuation on new line with line break
 103                         set current.value += ('\n' + line.value)
 104                         continue
 105                     else
 106                         set line.parent = current
 107                         _ current.children.push(line)
 108                 elif line.indent < current.indent
 109                     var parent = current.parent
 110                     while parent != null && line.indent < parent.indent
 111                         set parent = parent.parent
 112                     set line.parent = parent.parent
 113                     if parent.parent
 114                         _ parent.parent.children.push(line)
 115                     else
 116                         return
 117                             _ error
 118                                 @ 'Malformed tree, only one root note allowed.'
 119                                 @ line
 120                                 @ mTree
 121                 set current = line
 122                 set current.children = []
 123             return nodes
 124     function error
 125         param message
 126         param line
 127         param mTree
 128         set message = message + '\nNode ' + line.name + ' ' + (line.value || '') + ' row: ' + line.row + ' col: ' + line.col + '.\n Filepath: ' + mTree.uri
 129         return
 130             {
 131                 @ __is_error true
 132                 @ message message
 133                 @ source 'wizzi-mtree/lib/loader/nodifier'

 100             @ log

  37         # A refresh could be need for these reasons
  38         #
  39     m _updateEvalContext
  40         param mTreeBrickData

  42         # If the mTreeBrick do not receives parameters

  46         var args = mTreeBrickData.mTreeBrick.$args
  47         if args && args.indexOf('
  48             # Mixin call arguments may contain IttfMacros,
  49                 # in that case they must be interpolated.

  51                 # mixer mTreeBrick. We need its eval context for interpolation.
  52             checked_call_return( mixer_mTreeBrick_EvalContext)
  53                 _ this.getMTreeBrickEvalContext
  54                     @ mTreeBrickData.mTreeBrick.$mixerBrickKey
  55             try
  56                 # Then we create a temporary JsWizziContext and load it with the
  57                 # context values of both the global context and the mixer mTreeBrick
  58                 # eval context.
  59                 if JsWizziContext == null
  60                     set JsWizziContext = require('./jsWizziContext')

  62                 _ interpolateArgsContext.setValues(this.jsWizziContext.globalContext.getSettableValues())
  63                 _ interpolateArgsContext.setValues(mixer_mTreeBrick_EvalContext.getValues())

  65                 # if so, what does it means? Needs investigation.
  66                 # then we interpolate the arguments passed to the mixed mTree brick
  67                 set args = interpolate(args, interpolateArgsContext)
  68                 # log 'JsWizziEvalHelper interpolateArgs', mTreeBrickData.mTreeBrick.$args, args
  69             catch ex

  85                 @ args

  89             if item.isByRef

  91                 # value must be retrieved from the eval context of the mixer mTreeBrick

 447     runner( NewExpression)
 448         # log 'NewExpression.node', node
 449         if node.callee.type === 'Identifier'
 450             var l = node.arguments.length
 451             var args = []
 452             foreach item in node.arguments
 453                 checked_run( value,  NewExpression argument)
 454                     _ runner(item, ctx)
 455                 _ args.push(value)
 456             # log 'NewExpression.args', args
 457             if node.callee.name === 'String' && l === 0
 458                 return new String()
 459             elif node.callee.name === 'String' && l === 1
 460                 return new String(args[0])
 461             elif node.callee.name === 'Number' && l === 0
 462                 return new Number()
 463             elif node.callee.name === 'Number' && l === 1
 464                 return new Number(args[0])
 465             elif node.callee.name === 'Date' && l === 0
 466                 return new Date()
 467             elif node.callee.name === 'Date' && l === 1
 468                 return new Date(args[0])
 469             elif node.callee.name === 'Date' && l === 2
 470                 return new Date(args[0],args[1])
 471             elif node.callee.name === 'Date' && l === 3
 472                 return new Date(args[0],args[1], args[2])
 473             elif node.callee.name === 'Date' && l === 4
 474                 return new Date(args[0],args[1], args[2], args[3])
 475             elif node.callee.name === 'Date' && l === 5
 476                 return new Date(args[0],args[1], args[2], args[3], args[4])
 477             elif node.callee.name === 'Date' && l === 6
 478                 return new Date(args[0],args[1], args[2], args[3], args[4], args[5])
 479             elif node.callee.name === 'RegExp' && l === 1
 480                 return new RegExp(args[0])
 481             elif node.callee.name === 'Array' && l === 0
 482                 return new Array()
 483             elif node.callee.name === 'Array' && l === 1
 484                 return new Array(args[0])
 485             elif node.callee.name === 'Object' && l === 0
 486                 return new Object()
 487             elif node.callee.name === 'Object' && l === 1
 488                 return new Object(args[0])
 489             elif node.callee.name === 'Map' && l === 0
 490                 return new Map()
 491             elif node.callee.name === 'Map' && l === 1
 492                 return new Map(args[0])
 493             elif node.callee.name === 'Set' && l === 0
 494                 return new Set()
 495             elif node.callee.name === 'Set' && l === 1
 496                 return new Set(args[0])
 497             elif node.callee.name === 'RegExp' && l === 1
 498                 return new RegExp(args[0])
 499             elif node.callee.name === 'RegExp' && l === 2
 500                 return new RegExp(args[0], args[1])
 501             else
 502                 return
 503                     _ local_error
 504                         @ ctx
 505                         @ ('Builtin object (or number of arguments) not managed ' + node.callee.name + ', num arguments ' + l)

 507                         @ node
 508                         @ 'NewExpression'
 509         return
 510             _ local_error
 511                 @ ctx
 512                 @ 'Not implemented. NewExpression.node.callee.type: "' + node.callee.type + '"'

 514                 @ node
 515                 @ 'NewExpression'

src/ittf/lib/jswizzi/contextData.js.ittf



   1 module wizzi-mtree.jswizzi.ContextData
   2     kind jsfile
   3     import util
   4     var errors = require('./errors')
   5     var f_verify = require('./functions/verify')
   6     class ContextData
   7         ctor
   8             param kind
   9             param brickKey
  10             set this.kind = kind
  11             set this.brickKey = brickKey
  12             _ this.clear
  13         m clear
  14             set this.$freezed = false
  15             set this.functions
  16                 {
  17             set this.values
  18                 {
  19             set this.declares
  20                 {
  21             set this.functionsStack
  22                 [
  23             set this.valuesStack
  24                 [
  25             set this.declaresStack
  26                 [
  27             set this.builtInFunctions
  28                 {
  29             set this.builtInObjects
  30                 {
  31         m $freeze
  32             set this.$freezed = true
  33         m declare
  34             param name
  35             param init
  36             if name == '$' && this.$freezed
  37                 throw new errors.InvalidVariableNameError('The variable "$" cannot be declared on the global context after it has been freezed.')
  38             set this.declares[name] = true
  39             if typeof (init) !== 'undefined'
  40                 set this.values[name] = init
  41             # TODO debug only
  42             if f_verify.isObject(init) == false
  43                 # log 'ContextData declare', name, init, 'kind', this.kind, this.brickKey
  44         m undeclare
  45             param name
  46             if this.declares[name] == true
  47                 delete this.declares[name]
  48             if this.values[name] == true
  49                 delete this.values[name]
  50         m isDeclared
  51             param name
  52             # log 'wizzi-mtree.contextData.isDeclared', name, this.declares[name]
  53             if this.declares[name] == true
  54                 return true
  55             elif this.declaresStack.length > 0
  56                 backeach item in this.declaresStack
  57                     if item[name] == true
  58                         return true
  59                 return false
  60             else
  61                 return false
  62         m setValue
  63             param name
  64             param value
  65             if name == '$' && this.$freezed
  66                 throw new errors.InvalidVariableNameError('The variable "$" cannot be set on the global context after it has been freezed.')
  67             _ this.declare(name, value)
  68             # TODO debug only
  69             if f_verify.isObject(value) == false
  70                 # log 'ContextData setValue', name, value, 'kind', this.kind, this.brickKey
  71         m setValues
  72             param values
  73             set values = (values || {})
  74             for var k in values
  75                 _ this.declare
  76                     @ k
  77                     @ values[k]
  78         # Set value only if name is declared
  79         m put
  80             param name
  81             param value
  82             if this.declares[name] === true
  83                 set this.values[name] = value
  84                 return true
  85             else
  86                 return false
  87         m getValue
  88             param name
  89             if this.declares[name] == true
  90                 # log 'wizzi-mtree.contextData.getValue found for', name, this.kind, this.brickKey
  91                 return this.values[name]
  92             elif this.declaresStack.length > 0
  93                 backeach item in this.declaresStack
  94                     if item[name] == true
  95                         # log 'wizzi-mtree.contextData.getValue found for', name, this.kind, this.brickKey
  96                         return this.valuesStack[i][name]
  97             else
  98                 # log 'wizzi-mtree.contextData.getValue not found for', name, this.kind, this.brickKey
  99                 return undefined
 100         m getValues
 101             # TODO what if the stack has items ???
 102             return this.values
 103         m getSettableValues
 104             # TODO what if the stack has items ???
 105             var ret = {}
 106             for var k in this.values
 107                 if k != '$'
 108                     set ret[k] = this.values[k]
 109             return ret
 110         m declareFunction
 111             param name
 112             param fn
 113             set this.functions[name] = fn
 114         m getFunction
 115             param name
 116             if this.functions[name]
 117                 return this.functions[name]
 118             elif this.functionsStack.length > 0
 119                 backeach item in this.functionsStack
 120                     if item[name]
 121                         return item[name]
 122             else
 123                 # undefined
 124                 return this.functions[name]
 125         m setBuiltInFunction
 126             param name
 127             param value
 128             set this.builtInFunctions[name] = value
 129         m getBuiltInFunction
 130             param name
 131             return this.builtInFunctions[name]
 132         m push
 133             _ this.functionsStack.push(this.functions)
 134             _ this.valuesStack.push(this.values)
 135             _ this.declaresStack.push(this.declares)
 136             set this.functions = {}
 137             set this.values = {}
 138             set this.declares = {}
 139         m pop
 140             if this.functionsStack.length > 0
 141                 set this.functions = this.functionsStack.pop()
 142                 set this.values = this.valuesStack.pop()
 143                 set this.declares = this.declaresStack.pop()
 144         m dumpValues
 145             log 'Dump context value for debug', this.kind
 146             for var k in this.declares
 147                 if f_verify.isObject(this.values[k]) == false
 148                     log k, this.values[k]
 149         m getDeclareddumpValues
 150             log 'Dump context value for debug', this.kind
 151             for var k in this.declares
 152                 if f_verify.isObject(this.values[k]) == false
 153                     log k, this.values[k]
 154         m getDeclaredInfo
 155             var ret = []
 156             for var k in this.declares
 157                 if f_verify.isObject(this.values[k]) == false
 158                     _ ret.push(k + '=' + this.values[k])
 159                 else
 160                     _ ret.push(k + '= [object]')
 161             return ret.join(', ')
 162     set module.exports = ContextData

  24     function getEsprimaErrorLines
  25         param esprimaException
  26         param source
  27         var statements = source.split('\n')
  28         var start = Math.max(0, (esprimaException.lineNumber - 4))
  29         var end
  30             _ Math.min
  31                 @ statements.length
  32                 @ (esprimaException.lineNumber + 4)
  33         var ret
  34             [
  35         for var i = start; i < end; i++
  36             _ ret.push(formatLineNumber(i + 1) + ' ' + statements[i])
  37             if (i == esprimaException.lineNumber - 1)
  38                 var col = esprimaException.column
  39                 _ ret.push(spaces(col + 4) + '^ ' + esprimaException.description)
  40         return ret.join('\n')
  41     function spaces
  42         param num
  43         return Array(num + 1).join(" ")
  44     function formatLineNumber
  45         param num
  46         if num > 999
  47             return num
  48         if num > 99
  49             return ('0' + num)
  50         if num > 9
  51             return ('00' + num)
  52         return ('000' + num)

  12         m for

  19         m if

  26         m elif
  27             param text
  28             param node
  29             if this.line.length > 0
  30                 _ this.w()
  31             _ this.w('else if (' + text + ') {' + ' //' + node.id)
  32             _ this.indent()
  33         m else
  34             if this.line.length > 0
  35                 _ this.w()
  36             _ this.w('else {')
  37             _ this.indent()
  38         m while
  39             param text
  40             param node
  41             if this.line.length > 0
  42                 _ this.w()

  44             _ this.indent()
  45         m end
  46             if this.line.length > 0
  47                 _ this.w()
  48             _ this.deindent()
  49             _ this.w('}')
  50         m w
  51             param text
  52             var ind = spaces(this.indentValue * 4)
  53             _ this.stm.push(ind + this.line + (text || ''))
  54             set this.line = ''

  56         m write

  58             set this.line += (text || '')
  59         m indent
  60             set this.indentValue++
  61         m deindent
  62             set this.indentValue = Math.max(0, (this.indentValue - 1))
  63         m toCode
  64             if this.line.length > 0
  65                 _ this.w()
  66             return this.stm.join('\n')
  67         m getErrorLines
  68             param esprimaException
  69             var start = Math.max(0, (esprimaException.lineNumber - 4))
  70             var end
  71                 _ Math.min
  72                     @ this.stm.length
  73                     @ (esprimaException.lineNumber + 4)
  74             var ret
  75                 [

  77                 _ ret.push(formatLineNumber(i + 1) + ' ' + this.stm[i])
  78                 if (i == esprimaException.lineNumber - 1)
  79                     var col = esprimaException.column
  80                     _ ret.push(spaces(col + 4) + '* ' + esprimaException.description)
  81             return ret
  82     function spaces
  83         param num
  84         return Array(num + 1).join(" ")
  85     function formatLineNumber
  86         param num
  87         if num > 999
  88             return num
  89         if num > 99
  90             return ('0' + num)
  91         if num > 9
  92             return ('00' + num)
  93         return ('000' + num)

src/ittf/lib/loader/t/mTreeBrick/calcParamValues.js.ittf



   1 $group
   2     #
   3         # Rules
   4         # Node command format
   5         # > $params param1 [,param2 [,param-n]]
   6         # param   : [&]name[:type][|default]
   7         # &       : the paramater is an object passed by reference
   8         # name    : the name of the parameter to use in IttfMacro expressions
   9         # type    : the parameter type
  10         # one-of : string(default), integer, float, boolean, date, object (implicit
  11         # when '&' declared), macro (implicit, detected from IttfMacro delimiters
  12         # contained in the default value)
  13         # default : typed-value | @@null | @@undefined
  14         # // warning! `title|null` becomes title = "null" (the quoted string null)
  15         # // if you want title to be null then : `title|@@null`
  16         # string  : quotes are optional, example: `title|"my way"` and `title|my way` are the same
  17         # boolean : true | false
  18         # date    : yyyy/mm/dd
  19         # macro   : an IttfMacro can be passed as a parameter to a mixin, when the parameter
  20         # is referenced we have a double macro substitution
  21         # TODO verify, explain how this works, macro or macros can be partial
  22         # insides of the default value?
  23     m calcParamValues
  24         param args
  25         # string args
  26         # optional
  27         var mTreeBrickRoot = this.nodes[0]
  28         var params = this.$params
  29         var
  30             decl _paramArray
  31                 [
  32             decl _argsArray
  33                 [
  34         if verify.isNotEmpty(params)
  35             set _paramArray = params.trim().split(',')
  36         if verify.isNotEmpty(args)
  37             set _argsArray = args.trim().split(',')
  38         var result
  39             [
  40         for var i = 0; i < _paramArray.length; i++
  41             var
  42                 decl name
  43                 decl type = 'string'
  44                 decl defaultValue = null
  45                 decl value = null
  46                 decl hasparamvalue = false
  47                 decl hasdefaultvalue = false
  48             # a param may have the format
  49             # 1) name
  50             # 2) name|default
  51             # 3) name:type|default
  52             # valid types: string(default), integer, float, boolean, date
  53             var param_parts
  54                 _ _paramArray[i].trim()
  55                     ._ split(/[|]/)
  56             if param_parts.length > 2
  57                 return
  58                     _ local_error
  59                         @ 'MixinParamError'
  60                         @ 'calcParamValues'
  61                         @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ' , Argument ' + i + ' is malformed. Expected name[:type[|default]]'
  62                         @ mTreeBrickRoot
  63             if param_parts.length == 2
  64                 set defaultValue = param_parts[1].trim()
  65                 set hasdefaultvalue = true
  66             set param_parts
  67                 _ param_parts[0].trim()
  68                     ._ split(/[:]/)
  69             if param_parts.length > 2
  70                 return
  71                     _ local_error
  72                         @ 'MixinParamError'
  73                         @ 'calcParamValues'
  74                         @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', argument ' + i + ' is malformed. Expected name[:type[|default]]'
  75                         @ mTreeBrickRoot
  76             if param_parts.length == 2
  77                 set type = param_parts[1]
  78             set name = param_parts[0]
  79             if name.substr(0, 1) === '&'
  80                 set name = name.substr(1)
  81                 set type = 'object'
  82             if _argsArray.length > i
  83                 set value = _argsArray[i].trim()
  84                 if type === 'object'
  85                     if value.substr(0, 1) !== '&'
  86                         return
  87                             _ local_error
  88                                 @ 'MixinParamError'
  89                                 @ 'calcParamValues'
  90                                 @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', argument (' + i + ') must be an object reference. Found ' + value
  91                                 @ mTreeBrickRoot
  92                     else
  93                         set value = value.substr(1)
  94                 else
  95                     set value = verify.convert(value, type, true)
  96                     if value && value.__is_error
  97                         return
  98                             _ local_error
  99                                 @ 'MixinParamError'
 100                                 @ 'calcParamValues'
 101                                 @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', objectifying parameter: ' + i + '/' + name
 102                                 @ mTreeBrickRoot
 103                                 @ value
 104                 set hasparamvalue = true
 105             elif hasdefaultvalue
 106                 set value = verify.convert(defaultValue, type, true)
 107                 if value && value.__is_error
 108                     return
 109                         _ local_error
 110                             @ 'MixinParamError'
 111                             @ 'calcParamValues'
 112                             @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', converting parameter: ' + i + '/' + name + ' to type ' + type
 113                             @ mTreeBrickRoot
 114                             @ value
 115             else
 116                 return
 117                     _ local_error
 118                         @ 'MixinParamError'
 119                         @ 'calcParamValues'
 120                         @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', missing value for not optional argument ' + i + ' = ' + name
 121                         @ mTreeBrickRoot
 122             var isIttfMacro
 123                 iif type === 'object'
 124                     then false
 125                     else
 126                         _ verify.isIttfMacro(value)
 127             _ result.push
 128                 {
 129                     @ name
 130                         iif name.substr(0, 1) === '&'
 131                             then
 132                                 _ name.substr(1)
 133                             else name
 134                     @ value value
 135                     @ type type
 136                     @ isIttfMacro isIttfMacro
 137                     @ isByRef type === 'object'
 138         return result

src/ittf/lib/loader/ittfDocumentFinder.js.ittf

src/ittf/lib/loader/ittfInterpolate.js.ittf



   1 module wizzi-mtree.loader.interpolate
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var verify = require('wizzi-utils').verify
   4     var jsWizziRunner = require('../jswizzi/jsWizziRunner')
   5     #
   6         # rules:
   7         # Macro expressions are enclosed by ${'$'}{ and } delimiters.
   8         # example: ${'$'}{name}.
   9         # A macro expression can be escaped and used as a literal,
  10         # example: \${'$'}\{name}.
  11         # A macro expression may contain paired graphs { },
  12         # example: ${'$'}{ for { var i=0; i<10; i++} ; return i; }.
  13         # An empty macro ${} is treated as a literal, it is not replaced.
  14         # An unclosed delimiter 
  15     var state_text = 0
  16     var state_tag = 1
  17     var state_key = 2
  18     function interpolate
  19         param template
  20         param jsWizziContext
  21         param options
  22         if typeof template === 'undefined' || template === null
  23             return ''
  24         if typeof options === 'undefined' || options === null
  25             set options = {}
  26         var isCompile = options.isCompile
  27         var
  28             decl l = template.length
  29             decl result = []
  30             decl ch
  31             decl key
  32             decl inside_tags = 0
  33             decl state = state_text
  34             decl replacer = null
  35             decl keyOrCode
  36         if isCompile
  37             _ result.push("'")
  38         for var i=0; i<l; i++
  39             set ch = template[i]
  40             if ch == '\\'
  41                 # log 'wizzi-mtree.loader.ittfInterpolate', template[i+1], template[i+2], template[i+3]
  42             if state == state_text && ch == '\\' && i+3 < l && template[i+1] == '$' && template[i+2] == '\\' && template[i+3] == '{'
  43                 _ result.push('
  44                 set i = i +3
  45                 continue
  46             if ch == '$'
  47                 if state == state_text
  48                     set state = state_tag
  49                 elif state == state_key
  50                     _ key.push(ch)
  51                 else
  52                     # state == state_tag
  53                     # case double $$, is text
  54                     _ result.push('$$')
  55                     set state = state_text
  56             elif ch == '{'
  57                 if state == state_text
  58                     if isCompile && ch === "'"
  59                         _ result.push('\\')
  60                     _ result.push(ch)
  61                 elif state == state_key
  62                     # case '{' inside $ { }
  63                     set inside_tags++
  64                     _ key.push(ch)
  65                 else
  66                     # state == state_tag
  67                     # case 
  68                     set state = state_key
  69                     set key = []
  70                     set inside_tags = 0
  71             elif ch == '}'
  72                 if state == state_text
  73                     if isCompile && ch === "'"
  74                         _ result.push('\\')
  75                     _ result.push(ch)
  76                 elif state == state_key
  77                     if inside_tags > 0
  78                         # case '{}' inside $ { }
  79                         set inside_tags--
  80                         _ key.push(ch)
  81                     else
  82                         set keyOrCode = key.join('')
  83                         if keyOrCode.replace(/\s/g,'').length == 0
  84                             # case empty ${} - is ok do not replace
  85                             _ result.push('${}')
  86                         else
  87                             if isCompile
  88                                 _ result.push("' + " + keyOrCode + " + '")
  89                             else
  90                                 checked_call_return( replacer,  ittf.interpolate )
  91                                     _ evalKeyOrCode(keyOrCode, jsWizziContext)
  92                                 _ result.push(replacer)
  93                         set state = state_text
  94                 else
  95                     # state == state_tag
  96                     # case strange sequence '$}' but ok
  97                     _ result.push('$}')
  98                     set state = state_text
  99             else
 100                 if state == state_text
 101                     if isCompile && ch === "'"
 102                         _ result.push('\\')
 103                     _ result.push(ch)
 104                 elif state == state_key
 105                     _ key.push(ch)
 106                 else
 107                     # state == state_tag
 108                     # case sequence '$*' is text
 109                     _ result.push('$')
 110                     if isCompile && ch === "'"
 111                         _ result.push('\\')
 112                     _ result.push(ch)
 113                     set state = state_text
 114         # check for unclosed macros
 115         if state == state_key
 116             # 16/11/17 _ result.push('
 117             _ result.push('
 118         elif state == state_tag
 119             _ result.push('$')
 120         if isCompile
 121             _ result.push("'")
 122         return result.join('')
 123     function evalKeyOrCode
 124         param keyOrCode
 125         param jsWizziContext
 126         # log 'wizzi-mtree.loader.ittfInterpolate.evalKeyOrCode: ', keyOrCode
 127         var stm
 128             iif keyOrCode.indexOf('return ') > -1
 129                 then 'var _____result = function dummy() { ' + keyOrCode + ' }();'
 130                 else 'var _____result = ' + keyOrCode + ';'
 131         checked_call_return( notUsed,  ittf.interpolate.evalKeyOrCode )
 132             _ jsWizziRunner.run(stm, jsWizziContext)
 133         return jsWizziContext.getValue('_____result')
 134     set module.exports = interpolate

src/ittf/lib/loader/liner_save.js.ittf



   1 module wizzi-mtree.loader.liner
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var util = require('util')
   4     #
   5         # Reads an IttfDocument and extract an array of line descriptions
   6     #
   7         # params
   8         # string textContent
   9         # # The text content of the IttfDocument
  10         # { ittfDocumentData
  11         # string sourceKey
  12         # # The IttfDocument key generated by the loadHistory
  13     #
  14         # Output
  15         # lines:Array of
  16         # line : {
  17         # indent: Number,
  18         # name: String,
  19         # value: String, // always trimmed
  20         # row: Number,
  21         # col: Number,
  22         # sourceKey: String,
  23         # tagSuffix: undefined || '(',
  24         # hasMacro: Boolean
  25         # }
  26     #
  27         # Ittf commands for comments
  28         # $ and $ ... singleline comment
  29         # $ and * ... * and $ multiline comment
  30         # Comment states
  31         # 0 = no comment seen
  32         # 1 = seen char $ could be first char of comment
  33         # 2 = seen chars $ and * we are inside multiline comments
  34         # 3 = seen chars $ and * ... and *  could be first char of end of multiline comments
  35         # 21 = seen chars $ and $ we are inside singleline comment
  36         # Es6 macro states
  37         # 0 = no macro seen
  38         # 1 = seen char ` we are inside template
  39         # 2 = seen escape char inside a template, the next ` char does not close the macro string
  40         # 10 = seen char $ inside a template could be start of macro
  41     var COMMENT
  42         {
  43             @ NONE 0
  44             @ NONE_SEEN_DOLLAR 1
  45             @ MULTI_LINE 2
  46             @ MULTI_LINE_SEEN_ASTER 3
  47             @ SINGLE_LINE 21
  48     var MACRO
  49         {
  50             @ NONE 0
  51             @ INSIDE_TEMPLATE 1
  52             @ INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_ESCAPE 2
  53             @ INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_DOLLAR 10
  54     var CP
  55         {
  56             @ DOLLAR 36
  57             @ ASTER 42
  58             @ SLASH 92
  59             @ SINGLE_QUOTE 39
  60             @ DOUBLE_QUOTE 34
  61             @ TAB 9
  62             @ LF 10
  63             @ CR 13
  64             @ SPACE 32
  65     set module.exports
  66         function
  67             param textContent
  68             param ittfDocumentData
  69             var
  70                 decl sourceKey = ittfDocumentData.sourceKey
  71                 decl lines
  72                     [
  73                 decl leadingWhiteSpaces = 0
  74                 decl line = null
  75                 decl linepos = 1
  76                 decl lineHasMacro = false
  77                 decl colpos = 0
  78                 decl commentState = COMMENT.NONE
  79                 decl macroState = MACRO.NONE
  80                 decl quote = null
  81                 # TODO ensure textContent is red as utf-8 and avoid this
  82                 decl chunk = textContent.toString('utf-8')
  83                 decl ch
  84                 decl chUni
  85                 decl i
  86                 decl l = chunk.length
  87             # TODO replace ch with chUni
  88             for i = 0; i < l; i++
  89                 set ch = chunk[i]
  90                 set chUni = chunk.charCodeAt(i)
  91                 var cp = (chunk.charAt(index) + chunk.charAt(index + 1)).codePointAt(0)
  92                 if cp > 0xffff
  93                     log 'wizzi-mtree.loader.liner.cp > 0xffff'
  94                     set index += 1
  95                 set colpos++
  96                 if ch == '\\'
  97                     # log '+++++ wizzi-mtree.liner', chunk[i+1], chunk[i+2], chunk[i+3]
  98                 if quote != null
  99                     if quote == ch
 100                         set quote = null
 101                     _ processMacro(ch)
 102                 else
 103                     if commentState == COMMENT.MULTI_LINE $$ 2
 104                         if ch == '*'
 105                             # could be start of end of comment
 106                             set commentState = COMMENT.MULTI_LINE_SEEN_ASTER $$ 3
 107                         else
 108                             # skip comment char
 109                             if ch == '\n'
 110                                 set linepos++
 111                                 set colpos = 0
 112                     elif commentState == COMMENT.SINGLE_LINE $$ 21
 113                         if ch == '\n'
 114                             # end of line comment
 115                             # delegate end of comment to processMacro
 116                             _ processMacro(ch)
 117                     elif commentState == COMMENT.MULTI_LINE_SEEN_ASTER $$ 3
 118                         if ch == '$'
 119                             # ok, really is end of comment
 120                             set commentState = COMMENT.NONE $$ 0
 121                         else
 122                             # no, multi line comments continue
 123                             set commentState = COMMENT.MULTI_LINE $$ 2
 124                             # check if it is eol
 125                             if ch == '\n'
 126                                 set linepos++
 127                                 set colpos = 0
 128                     elif commentState == COMMENT.NONE_SEEN_DOLLAR && ch == '*'
 129                         # ok, really is start of multi line comment
 130                         set commentState = COMMENT.MULTI_LINE $$ 2
 131                     elif commentState == COMMENT.NONE_SEEN_DOLLAR && ch == '$'
 132                         # ok, is a single line comment
 133                         set commentState = COMMENT.SINGLE_LINE $$ 21
 134                     elif commentState == COMMENT.NONE_SEEN_DOLLAR && ch != '*'
 135                         # no, it was not a comment, reset
 136                         set commentState = COMMENT.NONE $$ 0
 137                         _ processMacro('$')
 138                         _ processMacro(ch)
 139                     elif commentState == COMMENT.NONE && ( ch == '"' || ch == "'" )
 140                         # start of literal
 141                         set quote = ch
 142                         _ processMacro(ch)
 143                     elif commentState == COMMENT.NONE && ch == '$'
 144                         # could be start of comment
 145                         set commentState = COMMENT.NONE_SEEN_DOLLAR $$ 1
 146                     elif ch == '\\' && i+3 < l && chunk[i+1] == '$' && chunk[i+2] == '\\' && chunk[i+3] == '{'
 147                         _ processChar('$')
 148                         _ processChar('{')
 149                         set i = i +3
 150                     else
 151                         _ processMacro(ch)
 152             if line
 153                 if typeof (line.value) !== 'undefined'
 154                     set line.value = line.value.trim()
 155                 set line.hasMacro = lineHasMacro
 156                 # log 'last push line', line
 157                 _ lines.push(line)
 158                 set lineHasMacro = false
 159             return lines
 160             function processMacro
 161                 param ch
 162                 if macroState == MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_ESCAPE $$ 2
 163                     # remove escape state
 164                     set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE $$ 1
 165                     _ processChar(ch)
 166                     # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 167                 elif macroState == MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_DOLLAR $$ 10
 168                     if ch == '{'
 169                         # ok - really it was a start of macro
 170                         # Alt+146 = Æ
 171                         _ processChar('Æ')
 172                         _ processChar('{')
 173                         set lineHasMacro = true
 174                     else
 175                         # no - it was not a start of macro
 176                         _ processChar('$')
 177                         _ processChar(ch)
 178                     set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE $$ 1
 179                     # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 180                 else
 181                     if chUni == 96
 182                         if macroState > MACRO.NONE $$ 0
 183                             set macroState = MACRO.NONE $$ 0
 184                             _ processChar(ch)
 185                             # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 186                         else
 187                             set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE $$ 1
 188                             _ processChar(ch)
 189                             # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 190                     else
 191                         if macroState == MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE $$ 1
 192                             if ch == '$'
 193                                 # could be start of macro
 194                                 set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_DOLLAR $$ 10
 195                                 # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 196                             elif ch == '\\'
 197                                 # could be an escape of a template start inside a template
 198                                 set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_ESCAPE $$ 2
 199                                 _ processChar(ch)
 200                                 # log 'macroState', macroState, ch
 201                             else
 202                                 # log 'process char macroState', macroState, ch
 203                                 _ processChar(ch)
 204                         else
 205                             _ processChar(ch)
 206             function processChar
 207                 param ch
 208                 if ch == '\n'
 209                     if line
 210                         if typeof (line.value) !== 'undefined'
 211                             set line.value = line.value.trim()
 212                         set line.hasMacro = lineHasMacro
 213                         _ lines.push(line)
 214                         set line = null
 215                         set lineHasMacro = false
 216                     else
 217                         # Allow blank line. Do nothing
 218                     set leadingWhiteSpaces = 0
 219                     set colpos = 0
 220                     set linepos++
 221                     set macroState = MACRO.NONE
 222                     if commentState != COMMENT.MULTI_LINE $$ 2
 223                         set commentState = COMMENT.NONE $$ 0
 224                 elif ch == '\r'
 225                 elif [' ', '\t'].indexOf(ch) !== -1
 226                     if ch == '\t'
 227                         set colpos += 3
 228                     if line
 229                         if typeof (line.value) == 'undefined'
 230                             set line.value = ''
 231                         else
 232                             set line.value += ch
 233                     else
 234                         set leadingWhiteSpaces += ch == ' ' ? 1 : 4
 235                 elif ['('].indexOf(ch) !== -1
 236                     if line
 237                         if typeof (line.value) == 'undefined'
 238                             set line.tagSuffix = ch
 239                             set line.value = ''
 240                         else
 241                             set line.value += ch
 242                     else
 243                         set line =
 244                             {
 245                                 @ indent leadingWhiteSpaces / 4
 246                                 @ name ch
 247                                 @ row linepos
 248                                 @ col colpos
 249                                 @ sourceKey sourceKey
 250                 else
 251                     if line
 252                         if typeof(line.value) == 'undefined'
 253                             set line.name += ch
 254                         else
 255                             set line.value += ch
 256                     else
 257                         set line =
 258                             {
 259                                 @ indent leadingWhiteSpaces / 4
 260                                 @ name ch
 261                                 @ row linepos
 262                                 @ col colpos
 263                                 @ sourceKey sourceKey
 264                 if line
 265                     # log 'line.name, value', line.name, line.value

   1 module wizzi-mtree.loader.liner
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var util = require('util')
   4     #
   5         # Reads an IttfDocument and extract an array of line descriptions
   6     #
   7         # params
   8         # string textContent
   9         # # The text content of the IttfDocument
  10         # { ittfDocumentData
  11         # string sourceKey
  12         # # The IttfDocument key generated by the loadHistory
  13     #
  14         # Output
  15         # lines:Array of
  16         # line : {
  17         # indent: Number,
  18         # name: String,
  19         # value: String, // always trimmed
  20         # row: Number,
  21         # col: Number,
  22         # sourceKey: String,
  23         # tagSuffix: undefined || '(',
  24         # hasMacro: Boolean
  25         # }
  26     #
  27         # Ittf commands for comments
  28         # $ and $ ... singleline comment
  29         # $ and * ... * and $ multiline comment
  30         # Comment states
  31         # 0 = no comment seen
  32         # 1 = seen char $ could be first char of comment
  33         # 2 = seen chars $ and * we are inside multiline comments
  34         # 3 = seen chars $ and * ... and *  could be first char of end of multiline comments
  35         # 21 = seen chars $ and $ we are inside singleline comment
  36         # Es6 macro states
  37         # 0 = no macro seen
  38         # 1 = seen char ` we are inside template
  39         # 2 = seen escape char inside a template, the next ` char does not close the macro string
  40         # 10 = seen char $ inside a template could be start of macro
  41     var COMMENT
  42         {
  43             @ NONE 0
  44             @ NONE_SEEN_DOLLAR 1
  45             @ MULTI_LINE 2
  46             @ MULTI_LINE_SEEN_ASTER 3
  47             @ SINGLE_LINE 21
  48     # https://hacks.mozilla.org/2015/05/es6-in-depth-template-strings-2/
  49     var MACRO
  50         {
  51             @ NONE 0

  63             @ SLASH 92

 134                         else

 137                             # check if it is eol

 140                                 set colpos = 0
 141                     elif commentState == COMMENT.NONE_SEEN_DOLLAR
 142                         if cp == CP.ASTER
 143                             # ok, is start of multi line comment
 144                             set commentState = COMMENT.MULTI_LINE
 145                         elif cp == CP.DOLLAR
 146                             # ok, is a single line comment
 147                             set commentState = COMMENT.SINGLE_LINE
 148                         else
 149                             # no, it was not a comment, reset
 150                             set commentState = COMMENT.NONE
 151                             _ processMacro(CP.DOLLAR)
 152                             _ processMacro(cp)
 153                     elif commentState == COMMENT.NONE && ( cp == CP.SINGLE_QUOTE || cp == CP.DOUBLE_QUOTE )

 157                         set quote = cp

 163                         _ processMacro(CP.DOLLAR)
 164                         _ processMacro(CP.OPEN_GRAPH)

 169                 if typeof (line.value) !== 'undefined'

 171                 set line.hasMacro = lineHasMacro
 172                 # log 'last push line', line
 173                 _ lines.push(line)
 174                 set lineHasMacro = false

 176             function processMacro
 177                 param cp
 178                 if macroState == MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_ESCAPE
 179                     # remove escape state
 180                     set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE
 181                     _ processChar(cp)
 182                     # log 'macroState', macroState, String.fromCodePoint(cp)
 183                 elif macroState == MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_DOLLAR
 184                     if cp == CP.OPEN_GRAPH
 185                         # ok - really it was a start of macro
 186                         # Alt+146 = Æ
 187                         _ processChar(CP.MACRO_REPLACE)
 188                         _ processChar(CP.OPEN_GRAPH)
 189                         set lineHasMacro = true
 190                     else
 191                         # no - it was not a start of macro
 192                         _ processChar(CP.DOLLAR)
 193                         _ processChar(cp)
 194                     set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE
 195                     # log 'macroState', macroState, String.fromCodePoint(cp)
 196                 else
 197                     if cp == CP.BACKTICK
 198                         if macroState > MACRO.NONE
 199                             set macroState = MACRO.NONE
 200                             _ processChar(cp)
 201                             # log 'macroState', macroState, String.fromCodePoint(cp)
 202                         else
 203                             set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE
 204                             _ processChar(cp)
 205                             # log 'macroState', macroState, String.fromCodePoint(cp)
 206                     else
 207                         if macroState == MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE
 208                             if cp == CP.DOLLAR
 209                                 # could be start of macro
 210                                 set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_DOLLAR
 211                                 # log 'macroState', macroState, String.fromCodePoint(cp)
 212                             elif cp == CP.SLASH
 213                                 # could be an escape of a template start inside a template
 214                                 set macroState = MACRO.INSIDE_TEMPLATE_SEEN_ESCAPE
 215                                 _ processChar(cp)
 216                                 # log 'macroState', macroState, String.fromCodePoint(cp)
 217                             else
 218                                 # log 'process char macroState', macroState, String.fromCodePoint(cp)
 219                                 _ processChar(cp)
 220                         else
 221                             _ processChar(cp)
 222             function processChar
 223                 param cp
 224                 if cp == CP.LF
 225                     if line
 226                         if typeof (line.value) !== 'undefined'
 227                             set line.value = line.value.trim()
 228                         set line.hasMacro = lineHasMacro
 229                         _ lines.push(line)
 230                         set line = null
 231                         set lineHasMacro = false
 232                     else
 233                         # Allow blank line. Do nothing

 235                     set colpos = 0

 238                     set quote = null
 239                     if commentState != COMMENT.MULTI_LINE

src/ittf/lib/loader/loadHistory.js.ittf



   1 module wizzi-mtree.loader.loadHistory
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var util = require('util')
   4     var MTreeBrickProvider = null
   5     #
   6         # One mTree loading uses 1 mTreeBrickProvider and 1 loadHistory.
   7         #
   8         # The loadHistory keeps tracks of the ittf documents loaded
   9         # for building one mTree. Once loaded, ittf documents become mTreeBricks,
  10         # that may be reused many times for the same mTree and always are cloned.
  11         # Every cloned mTreeBrick has its own evalContext and
  12         # the load context assigns source keys to ittf documents, loaded once, and
  13         # mTreeBrick keys to every cloned mTreeBricks.
  14         # It also checks the mix and include call chain to prevent recursion.
  15         #
  16         # ittfDocumentDatas: Map
  17         # key: sourceKey
  18         # item object:
  19         # string ittfDocumentUri
  20         # string content
  21         # string sourceKey
  22         #
  23         # mTreeBrickDatas: Map
  24         # key: brickKey
  25         # item object:
  26         # string ittfDocumentUri
  27         # string schema
  28         # { mTreeBrick (cloned)      // mTreeBrick is created by the mTreeBrickProvider
  29         # $mixerBrickKey:String    // key of the mixer mTreeBrickData
  30         # // set by the lib/loader/mixer
  31         # $args:String             // args of the mixin call
  32         # // set by the lib/loader/mixer
  33         # $params:String           // params received by the mixed mTreeBrick
  34         # byRefParams:Array        // params passed by reference
  35         # calcParamValues:Function  // calculates the values
  36         # { evalContext
  37         # string sourceKey
  38         # string brickKey
  39         #
  40         # [ callChain
  41         # {
  42         # string mixerUri
  43         # string mixedUri
  44         #
  45     wz-class LoadHistory
  46         ctor
  47             set this.__type = 'LoadHistory'

  97                 iif ittfDocumentData
  98                     then
  99                         set ittfDocumentData.ittfDocumentUri
 100                     else 'Source ittfDocumentUri unknown'
 101         m getSourceKey
 102             param ittfDocumentUri
 103             for var k in this.ittfDocumentDatas
 104                 if this.ittfDocumentDatas[k].ittfDocumentUri === ittfDocumentUri
 105                     return k
 106             return null
 107         m getIttfDocuments
 108             var ret
 109                 {
 110             for var k in this.ittfDocumentDatas
 111                 var ittfDocumentData = this.ittfDocumentDatas[k]
 112                 set ret[this.getIttfDocumentUri(ittfDocumentData.sourceKey)]
 113                     {
 114                         @ sourceKey ittfDocumentData.sourceKey
 115             return ret
 116         m getNewNodeId
 117             return ++this.nodeCount
 118         m enterFragmentCall
 119             param mixerUri
 120             param mixedUri
 121             _ this.callChain.push
 122                 {
 123                     @ mixerUri mixerUri
 124                     @ mixedUri mixedUri
 125         m exitFragmentCall
 126             _ this.callChain.pop()
 127         m checkForRecursion
 128             for var i = 0; i < this.callChain.length; i++
 129                 if this.callChain[i].mixerUri == this.callChain[i].mixedUri
 130                     return true
 131                 for var j = 0; j < this.callChain.length; j++
 132                     if ((this.callChain[j].mixerUri == this.callChain[i].mixedUri) && (this.callChain[j].mixedUri == this.callChain[i].mixerUri))
 133                         return true
 134             return false
 135         m _old_getLoadStateAsync_VIA

 163                                         if this.callChain[i].mixer == this.callChain[i].mixed
 164                                             return true

 166                                             if ((this.callChain[j].mixer == this.callChain[i].mixed) && (this.callChain[j].mixed == this.callChain[i].mixer))
 167                                                 return true

 209     function getFirstSemanticNode
 210         param nodes
 211         foreach node in nodes
 212             if node.name[0] != '$' || ((node.name === '$' || node.name === '$global') && node.value && node.value.length > 0)

   3     #
   4         # An mTreeBrick is a nodified ittf document.
   5         # In the build-up of an mTree, the same mTreeBrick can be mixed
   6         # or included many times, so it is created once then cloned.
   7         # { mTreeBrick
   8         # string uri       // The location of the source IttfDocument.
   9         # string schema    // The source IttfDocument schema.
  10         # { loadHistory    // The loadHistory object
  11         # [ lines          // parsed lines of source text
  12         # [ nodes          // nodified lines of source text
  13         # string sourceKey // key of the source info of the IttfDocument
  14         # string brickKey  // key of the cloned mTreeBrick
  15         #
  16         # ... these are set by the mixer, on the cloned object
  17         # boolean mixed          // true if has been mixed
  18         # string $mixerBrickKey  // the brickKey of the mTreeBrick of the calling node (mixer)
  19         # string $args           // the node-value of the mixer node
  20         # string $argArray       // the $arg array of the mixer node

  22         # ... these are set by the nodifier on the original mtree, then cloned
