src/ittf/lib/loader/nodifier.js.ittf



   1 module wizzi-mtree.loader.nodifier
   2     kind jsfile
   3     var util = require('util')
   4     #
   5         # Nodifies the lines of an IttfDocument and creates a
   6         # tree structure object based on line indentation.
   7         # . detects the $params command
   8         # . implements line continuation
   9         # . assigns an id to each node
  10         # !!! A line object is transformed in place into a node object
  11         # without recreation (no cloning) !!!
  12         #
  13         # Inputs
  14         # - the lines produced by the liner
  15         # - a newly created, empty, mTreeBrick
  16         # Outputs
  17         # [ nodes
  18         # { line -> mTreeNode
  19         # { parent
  20         # // parent mTreeNode
  21         # { model
  22         # // the mTreeBrick to which the line belongs
  23         # [ children
  24         # // the children mTreeNodes
  25         # id: Number,
  26         # indent: Number,
  27         # name: String,
  28         # value: String,
  29         # row: Number,
  30         # col: Number,
  31         # sourceKey: String,
  32         # tagSuffix: undefined || '('
  33         # hasMacro: Boolean
  34         #
  35         # Ittf commands:
  36         # $params  // the param values are stored in the MTree
  37         # \        // implements line continuation
  38         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  39         # //   without separators
  40         # \b       // implements line continuation
  41         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  42         # //   with a space separator:  prevLine,value += ' ' + currentLine.value
  43         # \n       // implements line continuation
  44         # //   the value is appendend to the value of the parent line
  45         # //   with a line break separator:  prevLine,value += '\n' + currentLine.value
  46         #
  47     set module.exports
  48         function
  49             [ lines
  50             { mTreeBrick
  51             var
  52                 decl nodes
  53                     [
  54                 decl root = null
  55                 decl current = null
  56                 decl nameFirstChar = null
  57                 decl nameLength = 0
  58                 decl line
  59                 decl i
  60                 decl l = lines.length
  61             for var i = 0; i < l; i++
  62                 set line = lines[i]
  63                 set nameFirstChar = line.name[0]
  64                 set nameLength = line.name.length
  65                 set line.id = mTreeBrick.loadHistory.getNewNodeId()
  66                 set line.model = mTreeBrick
  67                 if line.indent == 0 && current == null
  68                     set line.parent = null
  69                     _ nodes.push(line)
  70                 elif current == null
  71                     return
  72                         _ local_error
  73                             @ 'InvalidIttfError'
  74                             @ 'default'
  75                             @ 'Malformed tree, root node cannot have an indent.'
  76                             @ line
  77                             @ mTreeBrick
  78                 elif line.indent == current.indent
  79                     if typeof(current.parent) === 'undefined' || current.parent === null
  80                         return
  81                             _ local_error
  82                                 @ 'InvalidIttfError'
  83                                 @ 'default'
  84                                 @ 'Malformed tree, only one root note allowed.'
  85                                 @ line
  86                                 @ mTreeBrick
  87                     set line.parent = current.parent
  88                     _ current.parent.children.push(line)
  89                 elif line.indent > current.indent
  90                     if nameFirstChar == '$' && line.name === '$params'
  91                         if current.indent > 0
  92                             return
  93                                 _ local_error
  94                                     @ 'InvalidIttfError'
  95                                     @ 'default'
  96                                     @ 'The $params node must be a child of the root node.'
  97                                     @ line
  98                                     @ mTreeBrick
  99                         set current.model.$params = line.value
 100                         continue
 101                     elif nameFirstChar == '\\' && nameLength == 1
 102                         # value continuation on new line
 103                         set current.value += line.value
 104                         continue
 105                     elif nameFirstChar == '\\' && line.name === '\\b'
 106                         # value continuation on new line with space
 107                         set current.value += (' ' + line.value)
 108                         continue
 109                     elif nameFirstChar == '\\' && line.name === '\\n'
 110                         # value continuation on new line with line break
 111                         set current.value += ('\n' + line.value)
 112                         continue
 113                     else
 114                         set line.parent = current
 115                         _ current.children.push(line)
 116                 elif line.indent < current.indent
 117                     var parent = current.parent
 118                     while parent != null && line.indent < parent.indent
 119                         set parent = parent.parent
 120                     set line.parent = parent.parent
 121                     if parent.parent
 122                         _ parent.parent.children.push(line)
 123                     else
 124                         return
 125                             _ local_error
 126                                 @ 'InvalidIttfError'
 127                                 @ 'default'
 128                                 @ 'Malformed tree, only one root note allowed.'
 129                                 @ line
 130                                 @ mTreeBrick
 131                 set current = line
 132                 set current.children = []
 133             return nodes
 134     function local_error
 135         param name
 136         param method
 137         param message
 138         param line
 139         param mTreeBrick
 140         if line
 141             set message = message + '\nIn node: ' + line.name + ' ' + (line.value || '') + ' row: ' + line.row + ' col: ' + line.col + ' file: ' + mTreeBrick.uri
 142         return
 143             _ error
 144                 @ name
 145                 @ method
 146                 @ message

src/ittf/lib/loader/readme.md.ittf



   1 mdx
   2     h2 Glossary
   3     table
   4         md/glo-item( $append [hook-name] )
   5             span Is an ittf node command that declares a node branch that
   6                 + must be appended to a related '$hook [hook-name]' node command in
   7                 + a mixed mTree brick.
   8         md/glo-item( $hook [hook-name] )
   9             span Is an ittf node command that declares an insertion point in
  10                 + the tree structure of a mixed mTree brick. Node branches,
  11                 + children of a 'mix' node command, declared with the
  12                 + '$append [hook-name]' node command can be appended to the '$hook' node.
  13         md/glo-item( $include [path] )
  14             span Is an ittf node command that invokes the inclusion of another mTree brick.
  15                 + An include node command cannot have children nodes, and it is simply
  16                 + replaced by the included brick.
  17         md/glo-item( ittf document )
  18             span Ittf, short for Indented Text Tree Format, is the textual notation format of an mTree.
  19                 + An ittf document is a syntax tree, codified in a text document,
  20                 + where child nodes are indented to their parent.
  21                 + Every line is a node consisting of a name-value pair.
  22                 + The name is the first string of chars of the line and is separated
  23                 + from the value by a space or a tab.
  24                 + An ittf document is a template and when loaded for building an mTree
  25                 + we can pass a context object to the mTree loader.
  26                 + All nodes are templateable and composable. Even the root node may be a command node
  27                 + that invokes the mixup of its container.
  28                 + When parsed and nodified an ittf document become an mTree brick.
  29         md/glo-item( jsWizzi )
  30             span JsWizzi is a subset of the ECMA-262 javascript standard used by the wizzi factory
  31                 + for the buildup of mTrees.
  32                 + It is built on the quite efficent esprima parsing infrastructure and is run
  33                 + by a custom, sandboxed, javascript engine. See jsWizziRunner.
  34         md/glo-item( jsWizziContext )
  35             span The evaluation step of an mTree loading uses three types of value contexts.
  36             ul
  37                 li One global context.
  38                 li One single node structure context, where the mTree is built.
  39                 li One value context for each mTree brick.
  40         md/glo-item( jsWizziRunner )
  41             span The javascript engine of an mTree buildup. It is run for expressions interpolation,
  42                 + template commands evaluation and mTree final buildup.
  43         md/glo-item( mix node command )
  44             span Is an ittf node command that invokes the mixup of another mTree brick.
  45                 + Every node with the node-name ending with an open paren is a mix node command.
  46                 + A mix node command may have children nodes, that may declare
  47                 + branches to be appended to hooks in the mixed mTree brick.
  48                 + See the $append and $hook command nodes.
  49         md/glo-item( mTree )
  50             span An in-memory tree data structure of name-valued nodes that is built loading and
  51                 + processing an ittf document
  52         md/glo-item( mTree brick )
  53             span A nodified ittf document.
  54                 + mTree bricks are the items that compose an mTree.
  55                 + They can mix (or include) other bricks and be mixed (or included).
  56                 + The same brick can be reused in many branches of the mTree,
  57                 + so a brick is loaded once and always cloned.
  58         md/glo-item( - included mTree brick )
  59             span An mTree brick included in an including mTree brick
  60                 + using the node command <bold>$include [path]</bold>.
  61             p Both the tree structure and the value context are included.
  62                 + Context values declared in the included nodes are created in
  63                 + the scope of the includer.
  64         md/glo-item( - mixed mTree brick )
  65             span An mTree brick mixed in a mixing mTree brick
  66                 + using the node command <bold>[path]([params])</bold>.
  67             p The tree structure is mixed but the value context remain distinct.
  68                 + Context values declared in the mixed nodes are created in
  69                 + the scope of the mixed mTree brick and do not interfere with the mixer.
  70         md/glo-item( mTree loading )
  71             span The creation of an mTree from an ittf document.
  72             ul Loading steps
  73                 li line parsing (of a source ittf document)
  74                 li nodification (produces one mTree brick from every source ittf document)
  75                 li mix-composition (recursive on mixed and included mTree bricks)
  76                 li include-composition (recursive on mixed and included mTree bricks)
  77                 li append-resolution (on the composed mTree piece)
  78                 li evaluation (on the mixed and appended mTree piece)
  79         md/glo-item( - line parsing )
  80             span The text of the ittf document is parsed into name-valued lines,
  81                 + eliminating comments, resolving line continuations, detecting indentation
  82                 + and managing chars that interfere with variable interpolation.
  83         md/glo-item( - nodification )
  84             span The lines parsed in the previous step are transformed in a tree
  85                 + structure, an mTree brick, respecting the indentation of the source.
  86                 + One root node only is allowed.
  87         md/glo-item( - mix-composition )
  88             span The mTree brick, produced by the previous step, is traversed and
  89                 + all the 'mix node commands' encountered are recursively resolved.
  90                 + The result is an mTree piece composed by one or many bricks.
  91         md/glo-item( - include-composition )
  92             span The mTree piece, produced by the previous step, is traversed and
  93                 + all the '$include [path]' node commands encountered are recursively resolved.
  94                 + The recursion manages the mix-composition of included bricks too.
  95         md/glo-item( - append resolution )
  96             span The mTree piece resulting from composition is traversed again and
  97                 + child branches (of mix node commands), declared with the '$append [hook-name]'
  98                 + node command, are moved, replacing the related '$hook [hook-name]'
  99                 + node command of the mixed mTree brick.
 100         md/glo-item( - evaluation )
 101             span The last step of an mTree loading. From the mTree piece produced
 102                 + by the previous steps is created a jsWizzi script that evaluates
 103                 + the template commands of its nodes and builds the final mTree.
 104         md/glo-item( mTree buildup script )
 105             span The jsWizzi script that, once executed, by the
 106                 + jsWizziRunner, will give as result the final mTree
 107                 + of the source ittf document.
 108         md/glo-item( mTreeBuildUpScriptCoder)
 109             span A module of the wizzi.mtree package that generates the
 110                 + mTree build up script.
 111         md/glo-item( path resolution )
 112             span Include and mix command nodes declare the path of the ittf document
 113                 + that must be mixed or included. At first the path to match is built
 114                 + joining the current folder path of the calling document and the name
 115                 + of the callee document. If this match fails, then the 't' folder rule is applied,
 116                 + starting from the current folder path and going up on the folder tree.
 117                 + See 't' folder.
 118         md/glo-item( 't' folder )
 119             span Folders named 't' have special rules for the path resolution
 120                 + of mixed and included ittf documents. In the folder structure
 121                 + of a wizzi factory package, ittf documents contained in a 't' folder,
 122                 + can be referenced with the same rules that apply to nodejs packages
 123                 + in 'node_modules' folders. They are searched up on the folder tree, until the
 124                 + relative path of the mixin or include call is matched or the path resolution fails.

   9         function requireFromString
  10             param code
  11             param filename
  12             param opts
  13             if typeof filename === 'object'
  14                 set opts = filename
  15                 set filename = undefined
  16             set opts = opts || {}
  17             set filename = filename || ''
  18             set opts.appendPaths = opts.appendPaths || []
  19             set opts.prependPaths = opts.prependPaths || []
  20             if typeof code !== 'string'
  21                 throw new Error('code must be a string, not ' + typeof code)
  22             var paths = Module._nodeModulePaths(path.dirname(filename))
  23             var parent = module.parent;
  24             var m = new Module(filename, parent)
  25             set m.filename = filename
  26             set m.paths = [].concat(opts.prependPaths).concat(paths).concat(opts.appendPaths)
  27             _ m._compile
  28                 @ code
  29                 @ filename
  30             var exports = m.exports
  31             set parent.children && parent.children.splice(parent.children.indexOf(m), 1)
  32             return exports

   6     var md

   8             {
   9     #

  16     #
  17         # IttfCommands are nodes which name

  20     set md.findIttfCommand
  21         function
  22             param item
  23             param cmdname
  24             param cmdtype
  25             param startItem

  27                 # \b || (startItem && item.parent && item.parent.id === startItem.parent.id)
  28                 # searching the hook for an append command
  29                 # when descending from a parent we encounter startItem

  32             if item.name === ('$' + cmdtype)

  25                 _ parts.shift()
  26             if protocol.length === 1
  27                 if parts.length < 3
  28                     var_cb_error( InvalidRequest )
  29                         @ 'Invalid uri for an IttfDocument. Too short: ' + uri
  30                         @ 'UriError'
  31                 set ret.storeKind = 'filesystem'
  32                 set ret.userId = parts[0]
  33                 set ret.projectId = parts[1]
  34                 set ret.uri = uri
  35                 _ parts.shift()
  36                 _ parts.shift()
  37                 set ret.path = parts.join('/')
  38                 set name = parts[parts.length-1]
  39             elif protocol === 'repo'
  40                 if parts.length < 2
  41                     var_cb_error( InvalidRequest )
  42                         @ 'Invalid uri for an IttfDocument. Too short: ' + uri
  43                         @ 'UriError'
  44                 log 'parsedUri.parts', parts
  45                 log 'parsedUri', parsedUri
  46                 set ret.storeKind = 'repo'
  47                 set ret.userId = parsedUri.host
  48                 set ret.projectId = parts[0]
  49                 set ret.uri = uri
  50                 _ parts.shift();
  51                 set ret.path = parts.join('/')
  52                 set name = parts[parts.length-1]
  53             else
  54                 var_cb_error( InvalidRequest )
  55                     @ 'Invalid uri protocol for an IttfDocument. Must be a drive letter or "repo": uri=' + uri
  56                     @ 'UriError'
  57             var nameparts = name.split('.')
  58             if nameparts.length > 2 && nameparts[nameparts.length -1] === 'ittf'
  59                 set ret.isIttfDocument = true
  60                 set ret.schema = nameparts[nameparts.length -2]

  63             return
  64                 _ callback

  66                     @ ret

  32         _ runGroup(builtinFunctions)
  33     function runGroup
  34         param items
  35         foreach expr in items
  36             if typeof(expr.expected_equal) !== 'undefined'
  37                 tobe_eql( runExpression(expr.code),  expr.expected_equal )
  38             elif typeof(expr.expected_number) !== 'undefined'
  39                 tobe_number( runExpression(expr.code),  expr.expected_number )
  40             else
  41                 # log 'expr.code, expr.expected', expr.code, expr.expected
  42                 tobe_string_value( runExpression(expr.code),  expr.expected )
  43     function runExpression
  44         param code
  45         # without ctor arguments means: isForInterpolation
  46         var jsWizziContext
  47             new JsWizziContext()
  48         # run the expression embedded in a var declaration 'result'
  49         var hr
  50             _ jsWizziRunner.run
  51                 iif code.indexOf('return ') > -1
  52                     then 'var result = function dummy() { ' + code + ' }();'
  53                     else 'var result = ' + code + ';'
  54                 @ jsWizziContext
  55                 {
  56                     @ verbose false
  57         if hr && hr.__is_error
  58             throw new Error(hr)
  59         # return the 'result' var from the context
  60         return jsWizziContext.getValue('result')

src/ittf/lib/loader/t/mtreeBrick/calcParamValues.js.ittf



   1 $group
   2     #
   3         # Rules
   4         # Node command format
   5         # > $params param1 [,param2 [,param-n]]
   6         # param   : [&]name[:type][|default]
   7         # &       : the paramater is an object passed by reference
   8         # name    : the name of the parameter to use in IttfMacro expressions
   9         # type    : the parameter type
  10         # one-of : string(default), integer, float, boolean, date, object (implicit
  11         # when '&' declared), macro (implicit, detected from IttfMacro delimiters
  12         # contained in the default value)
  13         # default : typed-value | @@null | @@undefined
  14         # // warning! `title|null` becomes title = "null" (the quoted string null)
  15         # // if you want title to be null then : `title|@@null`
  16         # string  : quotes are optional, example: `title|"my way"` and `title|my way` are the same
  17         # boolean : true | false
  18         # date    : yyyy/mm/dd
  19         # macro   : an IttfMacro can be passed as a parameter to a mixin, when the parameter
  20         # is referenced we have a double macro substitution
  21         # TODO verify, explain how this works, macro or macros can be partial
  22         # insides of the default value?
  23     m calcParamValues
  24         param args
  25         # string args
  26         # optional
  27         var mTreeBrickRoot = this.nodes[0]
  28         var params = this.$params
  29         var
  30             decl _paramArray
  31                 [
  32             decl _argsArray
  33                 [
  34         if verify.isNotEmpty(params)
  35             set _paramArray = params.trim().split(',')
  36         if verify.isNotEmpty(args)
  37             set _argsArray = args.trim().split(',')
  38         var result
  39             [
  40         for var i = 0; i < _paramArray.length; i++
  41             var
  42                 decl name
  43                 decl type = 'string'
  44                 decl defaultValue = null
  45                 decl value = null
  46                 decl hasparamvalue = false
  47                 decl hasdefaultvalue = false
  48             # a param may have the format
  49             # 1) name
  50             # 2) name|default
  51             # 3) name:type|default
  52             # valid types: string(default), integer, float, boolean, date
  53             var param_parts
  54                 _ _paramArray[i].trim()
  55                     ._ split(/[|]/)
  56             if param_parts.length > 2
  57                 return
  58                     _ local_error
  59                         @ 'MixinParamError'
  60                         @ 'calcParamValues'
  61                         @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ' , Argument ' + i + ' is malformed. Expected name[:type[|default]]'
  62                         @ mTreeBrickRoot
  63             if param_parts.length == 2
  64                 set defaultValue = param_parts[1].trim()
  65                 set hasdefaultvalue = true
  66             set param_parts
  67                 _ param_parts[0].trim()
  68                     ._ split(/[:]/)
  69             if param_parts.length > 2
  70                 return
  71                     _ local_error
  72                         @ 'MixinParamError'
  73                         @ 'calcParamValues'
  74                         @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', argument ' + i + ' is malformed. Expected name[:type[|default]]'
  75                         @ mTreeBrickRoot
  76             if param_parts.length == 2
  77                 set type = param_parts[1]
  78             set name = param_parts[0]
  79             if name.substr(0, 1) === '&'
  80                 set name = name.substr(1)
  81                 set type = 'object'
  82             if _argsArray.length > i
  83                 set value = _argsArray[i].trim()
  84                 if type === 'object'
  85                     if value.substr(0, 1) !== '&'
  86                         return
  87                             _ local_error
  88                                 @ 'MixinParamError'
  89                                 @ 'calcParamValues'
  90                                 @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', argument (' + i + ') must be an object reference. Found ' + value
  91                                 @ mTreeBrickRoot
  92                     else
  93                         set value = value.substr(1)
  94                 else
  95                     set value = verify.convert(value, type, true)
  96                     if value && value.__is_error
  97                         return
  98                             _ local_error
  99                                 @ 'MixinParamError'
 100                                 @ 'calcParamValues'
 101                                 @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', objectifying parameter: ' + i + '/' + name
 102                                 @ mTreeBrickRoot
 103                                 @ value
 104                 set hasparamvalue = true
 105             elif hasdefaultvalue
 106                 set value = verify.convert(defaultValue, type, true)
 107                 if value && value.__is_error
 108                     return
 109                         _ local_error
 110                             @ 'MixinParamError'
 111                             @ 'calcParamValues'
 112                             @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', converting parameter: ' + i + '/' + name + ' to type ' + type
 113                             @ mTreeBrickRoot
 114                             @ value
 115             else
 116                 return
 117                     _ local_error
 118                         @ 'MixinParamError'
 119                         @ 'calcParamValues'
 120                         @ 'Error evaluating: $params ' + params + ', missing value for not optional argument ' + i + ' = ' + name
 121                         @ mTreeBrickRoot
 122             var isIttfMacro
 123                 iif type === 'object'
 124                     then false
 125                     else
 126                         _ verify.isIttfMacro(value)
 127             _ result.push
 128                 {
 129                     @ name
 130                         iif name.substr(0, 1) === '&'
 131                             then
 132                                 _ name.substr(1)
 133                             else name
 134                     @ value value
 135                     @ type type
 136                     @ isIttfMacro isIttfMacro
 137                     @ isByRef type === 'object'
 138         return result
